@sparsick 
I'm aware of that in core Java there is no relation between String and Iterables. But in AssertJ there is an [EnumerableAssert](https://github.com/joel-costigliola/assertj-core/blob/master/src/main/java/org/assertj/core/api/EnumerableAssert.java) interface which is a common interface for the string, array, iterables and some other assertion classes.

In my PR I added the new methods to EnumerableAssert and I implemented the methods for all child classes.
